**Lift `owner` out of the `try` block to fix scope error and ensure anon-session cookie on all responses.**

`owner` is declared inside the `try` block (line 82) but referenced in the `catch` block (line 228), causing a TypeScript compilation error. Additionally, the validation error path (lines 88-93) bypasses the `withAnonSessionCookie` helper that other paths use, reintroducing session fragmentation for anonymous requests during input validation.

<details>
<summary>Suggested fix</summary>

